data.title: Detroit Pistons' Tayshaun Prince checks in at No. 144 in ESPN.com ratings, ahead of Ben Gordon
data.meta_description: Greg Monroe and Rodney Stuckey will be the two highest-ranked Pistons and will appear somewhere in the top 140.
data.text:
Tayshaun Prince became the second Detroit Pistons starter to check in with ESPN.com's top 500 NBA players when the website ranked him No. 144.

The ranking was 39 spots lower than the No. 105 spot Prince logged in last summer's ratings and 10 spots ahead of Ben Gordon, whom the Pistons traded to Charlotte during this offseason.

ESPN.com polled 104 experts to rank players on a 1-10 scale in terms of "the current quality of each player," according to the website.

Prince scored 4.85.

Brandon Knight became the Pistons' first likely starter disclosed on the list when he placed 177th.

Likely starters Greg Monroe and Rodney Stuckey are the only Pistons whose positions have not been announced.

Previous Pistons in the rankings included Jonas Jerebko (206), Corey Maggette (221), Jason Maxiell (241), Will Bynum (244), Austin Daye (245), Charlie Villanueva (262), Andre Drummond (277), Ben Wallace (303), Kyle Singler (407), Kim English (441) and Khris Middleton (488).
